The towns of the jurisdiction of Hispalis are Celti, Axati, Arua, Canama, Evia, Ilipa surnamed Ilpa Italica3 on the left bank is the colony Hispal sur- named Romulensis, while on the opposite side are the towns Osset surnamed Julia Constantia, Ver- gentum or Juli Genius, Orippo, Caura, Siarum, and the river Maenuba, a tributary of the Guadal- quivir on its right. Between the estuaries of the Guadalquivir are the towns of Nabrissa, surnamed Veneria, and Colobana, with two colonies, Hasta, which is called Regia, and inland Asido, which is called Caesarina.

The river Xenil, joining the Guadalquivir at the place in the list already mentioned, washes the colony of Astigi, surnamed Augusta Firma, from which point it becomes navigable.
